## Differences Between USDT-M and USDS-M

### Leverage & Position Limits

| Feature | USDT-M | USDS-M |
|---------|--------|--------|
| **Max Leverage** | 20x | 20x (but different by symbol) |
| **Notional Limit** | $50,000 | Varies by symbol |
| **Min Notional** | $10 | $10 |
| **Initial Margin** | Varies | Varies |
| **Maintenance Margin** | Varies | Varies |

**Action:** Check Binance API `/fapi/v1/exchangeInfo` endpoint for exact limits per symbol.

### Collateral

| Feature | USDT-M | USDS-M |
|---------|--------|--------|
| **Collateral** | USDT | USDS |
| **Account Separated** | No (same account) | YES (separate account) |
| **Cross Margin** | Available | Available |
| **Isolated Margin** | Available | Available |

**Action:** Fund a separate USDS-M account. Don't assume your USDT-M balance transfers.

### Settlement & Funding

| Feature | USDT-M | USDS-M |
|---------|--------|--------|
| **Funding Intervals** | 8 hours (0:00, 8:00, 16:00 UTC) | Same as USDT-M |
| **Funding Rate** | Different | Different (track separately) |
| **Settlement** | USDT | USDS |

**Action:** Monitor funding rates separately for USDS-M; they may differ significantly.

