## Testnet vs Mainnet Trading

### Testnet (wss://stream.binancefuture.com)

**Pros:**
- Free to test
- No real money at risk
- Same API as mainnet
- Good for strategy validation

**Cons:**
- Limited USDS funding
- Lower volume/liquidity
- Fills may be different
- No real slippage

**Recommendation:** 
- Test all strategies on testnet first
- Run for at least 1 week to validate
- Check both BUY and SELL signals
- Verify stop-loss triggers work

### Mainnet (wss://fstream.binance.com)

**Pros:**
- Real market conditions
- Realistic fills and slippage
- Real funding rates

**Cons:**
- Real money at risk
- Real volatility and risk
- Cannot rewind/test "what-if"

**Recommendation:**
- Start with paper trading on mainnet data
- Use strict risk parameters initially
- Gradually increase position size
- Monitor actively for first week

