## Configuration Best Practices

### 1. Start Conservative

```bash
# Begin with small positions and strict limits
TRADING_LEVERAGE=3.0
MAX_DAILY_LOSS_PCT=0.02    # 2%
MAX_DRAWDOWN_PCT=0.05       # 5%
MAX_POSITION_PCT=0.10       # 10%
KELLY_FRACTION=0.10         # 10%
MIN_ORDER_QTY=0.01
```

### 2. Monitor for One Week

- Check daily P&L
- Review all trades
- Verify risk limits work
- Check for unexpected behavior
- Monitor logs for errors

### 3. Gradually Increase (if Profitable)

Week 2: Increase parameters by 20%
Week 3: Increase parameters by 30%
Week 4+: Increase to desired levels

### 4. Never Skip Testnet

- Always test new strategies on testnet first
- Test configuration changes
- Verify API connectivity
- Test emergency scenarios

### 5. Automate Monitoring

Set up alerts for:
- Daily loss limit approaching
- Drawdown exceeding thresholds
- API errors
- WebSocket disconnections
- Unusual trade fills

